headline: Tesla Stock vs. Amazon Stock: Billionaires Buy One and Sell the Other Ahead of 2025
summary: Tesla (NASDAQ: TSLA) and Amazon (NASDAQ: AMZN) are included in that number, with shares advancing 57% and 49%, respectively.  Louis Bacon of Moore Capital Management bought 25,000 shares of Tesla, increasing his position by 19%.  Meanwhile, he sold 616,475 shares of Amazon, reducing his stake by 76%.
